Explanation
Obstacle Avoiding Robotic Vehicle — Component Explanation

Arduino Uno — The brain of the robot; processes sensor data and sends commands to the motor driver and servo.
HC-SR04 Ultrasonic Sensor — Measures distance to obstacles by emitting ultrasonic pulses and calculating the echo return time.
SG90 Servo Motor — Rotates the ultrasonic sensor left and right to scan the surroundings for a wider field of view.
L298N Motor Driver — Acts as a bridge between Arduino and the DC motors, controlling speed and direction of both wheels.
2× DC Gear Motors — Drive the left and right wheels, enabling forward, backward, and turning motion.
Robot Chassis + Wheels — The physical frame that holds all components together and provides the rolling base.
Caster Wheel — A free-rotating support wheel at the front/rear that provides balance and smooth movement.
Breadboard — Used for making temporary circuit connections without soldering.
Jumper Wires — Connect all components together across the breadboard and Arduino pins.
Li-Ion Battery + Case — Powers the entire robot, offering a rechargeable and stable power supply.
